# Skill 11 Lesson 08.5 – Applying New Castle Rysen Subnet Strategy

## Overview

This lesson demonstrates how to implement a previously designed VLSM addressing scheme on a real Packet Tracer network.

Instead of only calculating subnets, the new addressing plan is deployed by updating router interfaces, switch management interfaces, NAT, DHCP, and verifying end-to-end connectivity.

---

## Learning Objectives

- Apply a VLSM subnet design to a live network
- Assign logical IP addresses to infrastructure devices
- Update router interface addressing
- Reconfigure NAT for the new subnet
- Configure DHCP for automatic client addressing
- Update switch management IP addresses
- Verify network connectivity using Cisco IOS commands

---

## Network Information

| Item | Value |
|------|-------|
| LAN Network | 10.0.18.0/26 |
| Subnet Mask | 255.255.255.192 |
| Default Gateway | 10.0.18.1 |
| Public Network | 216.0.5.0/24 |

