## Files

### theory.md

Contains the theoretical concepts covered in the lesson, including:

- Applying subnet strategies
- Logical IP addressing
- Infrastructure address planning
- DHCP concepts
- NAT updates
- Deployment best practices

---

### lab.md

Contains the complete Packet Tracer implementation:

- Router configuration
- NAT updates
- DHCP configuration
- Switch management configuration
- Verification commands
- Expected results

---

### configs/

Contains the running configuration of every configured device.

Example:

- cafe01-RT01-running-config.txt
- cafe01-SW01-running-config.txt
- cafe01-SW02-running-config.txt

---

### screenshots/

Contains screenshots of:

- Final topology
- Routing table
- NAT statistics
- DHCP operation
- Ping verification
- Switch MAC tables

---

## Verification Commands

Router

- show ip interface brief
- show ip route
- show ip nat statistics
- show ip nat translations
- show access-lists
- show running-config | include nat

Switch

- show ip interface brief
- show mac-address-table
- ping 10.0.18.1

